President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. R. Clarke Cooper of Florida is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of State for Political-Military Affairs. Cooper has a background in intergovernmental affairs, foreign policy, counter-terrorism, and rule of law, coupled with extensive operational experience. Daniel N. Rosenblum of Maryland is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Uzbekistan. Rosenblum has served in senior government positions for over two decades, managing people and resources, leading negotiations, and building consensus. Stephanie Sanders Sullivan of Maryland is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Ghana. Sullivan is a career diplomat with extensive experience in Africa, and she has previously served as the United States Ambassador to the Republic of Congo. Karen L. Williams of Missouri is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Suriname. Williams has served as a diplomat since 1991 and has held various overseas diplomatic postings.